-- Iran to Lead Exploration of Twelve Bolivian Oil, Gas Blocks, Aftab Reports
-- Ladane Nasseri
-- 2010-06-15T06:03:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/iran-to-lead-exploration-of-twelve-bolivian-oil-gas-blocks-aftab-reports.html

          
          
             Iran will take charge of the
exploration of 12 Bolivian oil and gas blocks,  Aftab  reported,
citing an oil ministry official.  
 Iran signed an agreement with Bolivia to cooperate on the
drilling, exploration, petrochemicals and in oil and gas
industries, the newspaper said, citing deputy Oil Minister for
International Affairs and Trade, Hassan Ahmadian.  
 Iran will also start exporting petrochemicals to Ecuador
“soon,” Ahmadian said, without providing further details.  
